==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: centralized
<hw>centralized</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>drawn toward a
center or brought under the control of a central authority; <as>as,
<ex>centralized</ex> control of emergency relief efforts</as>;
<ex>centralized</ex> government. Opposite of
<ant>decentralized</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>concentrated on or clustered around a central point
or purpose; -- contrasting with <contr>distributed</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> centered, centred, focused.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>centralizing</ent>⟦br⟧
